romanUrduTranslationText:
Bole, “Kyā	 sach	 much	 āap	 hi	 Yūsuf haiñ?
Kahā	maiñ	Yūsuf hooñ	aur	yeh	merā	bhāi;
be-shak	Allāh	 ne	 ham	 par	ehsān	 kiyā	 beshak		jo	parhezgāri	aur	sabr	kare	to	Allāh	nekoñ	kā	neg		(Ajr)	zāye	nahiñ	kartā”

englishTranslationText:
“O	my	Lord!	you	have	given	me	a	kingdom	*	and	have	taught	me	how	to	interpret	some	events;	
O	Creator	of	the	heavens	and	the	earth	- you	are	my	Supporter	in	the	world	and	in	the	Hereafter;	
cause	 me	 to	 die	 as	 a	 Muslim,	 and	 unite	 me	 with	 those	 who	 deserve	 Your	 proximity.”	 (* 
Prophethood and the rule over Egypt. Prophet Yusuf said this prayer while his death 
approached him.)
